records.addlTxt:
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the state, the Court ordered Count 2 DISMISSED. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State and defense.  Defendant makes no statement.
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 7 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber Release for employment only, Consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 7 days served. 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment if deemed necessary;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with Telly Hunt, Tamel Manns, Jhatara Clark, Tatiana Robinson, and Rudell Wilder;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Obtain high school diploma, GED, or HSED;
*Participate in Thinking for a Change program or a Cognitive Thinking program;
*No driving without a valid license;
*No weapons;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment. 

The Court grants expungement CONTINGENT upon successful completion of ALL conditions of probation (including financial obligations) by the end of the probation period.  Appeal rights given by the Court.
